Prerequisite: Python 3.X

To Encrypt the plain text, run the below command:
$ ./Encrypt_Caesar.py "Your_plain_text_goes_here" [enter_the_shift_key]
Note: Make sure you input the plain text in lowercase format. 

To Decrypt the plain text, run the below command:
$ ./DecryptCeaser.py "Your_cipher_text_goes_here" [Enter_the_shift_key]
Example:
└─$ ./DecryptCeaser.py "gwjfp ymnx nk dtz hfs" 5  

Cipher text: gwjfp ymnx nk dtz hfs
Shift pattern: 5
Plain text: BREAK THIS IF YOU CAN


To Bruteforce the cipher text with all possible shift keys, run the below command:
$ ./BruteForce_Ceaser.py "Your_Cipher_text_goes_here"
Example: 
└─$ ./BruteForce_Ceaser.py "LGEGJJGO OW OADD ESJUZ GF HSFLZWJ VAFAFY" 

Cipher text: lgegjjgo ow oadd esjuz gf hsflzwj vafafy
